2.2 Variables 
Variable naming follows C conventions: identifiers must begin with a letter or underscore and may 
contain letters, digits, and underscores (e.g. a, b, d3, d_3, myVar). Names are case-sensitive and 
keywords are reserved. Three usage patterns are supported: 
• Declaration:     int a; 
• Assignment:      a = 10; 
• Initialization:  int a = 10; 
